HEADWORD: Cornet--piston
<hw>Cor"net-⟦agrave⟧-pis`ton</hw> <pr>(k?r"n?t-?-p?s"t?n; F.
k?r`n?`?p?s`<er>t?n</er>")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Cornets-⟦agrave⟧-piston</plw>.</plu> <ety>[F.]</ety>
<fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A brass wind instrument, like the trumpet,
furnished with valves moved by small pistons or sliding rods; a
cornopean; a cornet.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

